  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Clans/Gouken.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting at 11th level, you gain a technique that you can use to empower your battle techniques. You gain an additional technique at 15th level, and another at 17th level:</p><ul data-start=\"218\" data-end=\"1381\"><li data-start=\"218\" data-end=\"561\"><p data-start=\"220\" data-end=\"561\"><strong data-start=\"220\" data-end=\"230\">Kikai!</strong> - You let out a powerful battle scream. As an action, you may expend any number of Ki Dice, each creature within 30ft of you must make a Wisdom Saving throw against your Ninjutsu save DC, gaining 2 ranks of fear and taking damage equal to the Ki Dice expended, or half as much and suffering no additional effects on a failed save.</p></li><li data-start=\"565\" data-end=\"875\"><p data-start=\"567\" data-end=\"875\"><strong data-start=\"567\" data-end=\"584\">Battle Weave:</strong> As a reaction to casting a Jutsu with the HS property, you may expend a number of Ki Dice equal to the Rank, it loses the HS property. Additionally, you may double the expended dice, and if you do, creatures cannot take reactions until the conclusion of the Jutsu. (D=1, C=2, B=3, A=4, S=5)</p></li><li data-start=\"877\" data-end=\"1024\"><p data-start=\"879\" data-end=\"1024\"><strong data-start=\"879\" data-end=\"903\">Resolve of the Body:</strong> As a full turn action, you may expend any number of Ki Dice, you heal a number of Hit Points equal to the amount rolled.</p></li><li data-start=\"1026\" data-end=\"1184\"><p data-start=\"1028\" data-end=\"1184\"><strong data-start=\"1028\" data-end=\"1052\">Resolve of the Mind:</strong> As a full turn action, you may expend any number of Ki Dice, you restore a number of Chakra Points equal to half the amount rolled.</p></li><li data-start=\"1186\" data-end=\"1381\"><p data-start=\"1188\" data-end=\"1381\"><strong data-start=\"1188\" data-end=\"1205\">True Strikes:</strong> As a bonus action, you may expend any number of Ki Dice, until the end of your turn, the next attack roll you make gains a bonus equal to the number of Dice Expended this way.</p></li></ul>",
